    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-01T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="530"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1660a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="35" xml:id="d530fn35">Repeated on the same date to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union as No. 938.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-01T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 1, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1407. Shipment of Lend-Lease supplies for China by the Turk-Sib Railway and
                    overland route. For your information, Tehran reports that according to the
                    British Minister two convoys of Lend-Lease supplies consisting largely of small
                    arms and ammunition have arrived at Meshed but that entry into Russia has been
                    refused. From Calcutta Schaberg of Lend-Lease reports that the Russian
                    representatives there have indefinitely canceled arrangements to ship Chinese
                    supplies over this route on the grounds that they cannot handle movement at the
                    present time.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
